Heat the oil in small saucepan over a medium heat. Add the onion and cook for 2â€“3 minutes. Add the garlic, ginger and carrots and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.Add the stock and season with pepper to taste. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes, or until the carrots are soft.Pour the soup into a food processor and blend until smooth. Return to the pan and reheat gently.To serve, pour the soup into a warm serving bowl and garnish with the spring onions.